{
  "answer": "The poem is **\"Tanhai\"** (Solitude), the 25th chapter (or poem) in *Bang-E-Dara Part 2* by Allama Iqbal.[^1]\n\nIt consoles a solitary heart by presenting the night sky's stars as its companions, the slumbering natural world (sky, earth, moon, desert, vale, and mountains) as a \"wild rose garden,\" and Nature itself as the heart's kindred spirit. The specified couplet appears as follows:\n\n> These lovely pearls, so bright they are,  \n> Are but your tears, become a star.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [chapter 25](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/25-tanhai/translation/).\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/25-tanhai/translation/#p-36f218).",
